<section class="section" style="background-color: var(--color-white);">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Platform Examples</h2>
    
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="card" style="background-color: var(--color-primary); color: var(--color-white);">
        <h3 class="card-title" style="color: var(--color-white);">Windows Phone Metro</h3>
        <p class="card-content" style="color: var(--color-white);">
          <strong>Year:</strong> 2010<br><br>
          First major flat design platform. Live tiles with bold typography. No shadows or 
          gradients. Inspired by Swiss design and airport signage.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="card" style="background-color: var(--color-success); color: var(--color-white);">
        <h3 class="card-title" style="color: var(--color-white);">iOS 7</h3>
        <p class="card-content" style="color: var(--color-white);">
          <strong>Year:</strong> 2013<br><br>
          Apple's dramatic shift from skeuomorphism. Translucent layers, flat colors, thin fonts. 
          Most influential flat design implementation.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="card" style="background-color: var(--color-warning); color: var(--color-white);">
        <h3 class="card-title" style="color: var(--color-white);">Windows 8</h3>
        <p class="card-content" style="color: var(--color-white);">
          <strong>Year:</strong> 2012<br><br>
          Full Metro design on desktop. Tile-based start screen. Completely flat interface 
          controversial but influential.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" style="background-color: var(--color-neutral);">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Web Applications</h2>
    
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="card-title" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Flat UI Pro</h3>
        <p class="card-content">
          <strong>Company:</strong> Designmodo<br>
          <strong>Year:</strong> 2013<br><br>
          Influential UI kit that popularized flat design for web. Defined the "Flat UI" 
          color palette still used today. Thousands of designers adopted these patterns.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="card-title" style="color: var(--color-success);">Spotify (2013 redesign)</h3>
        <p class="card-content">
          <strong>Platform:</strong> Web & Mobile<br>
          <strong>Year:</strong> 2013<br><br>
          Embraced flat aesthetic with bold album art and simple controls. Vibrant colors 
          without depth effects. Clean, modern music interface.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="card-title" style="color: var(--color-warning);">Facebook (2013-2014)</h3>
        <p class="card-content">
          <strong>Platform:</strong> iOS & Web<br>
          <strong>Year:</strong> 2013-2014<br><br>
          Simplified interface removing gradients. Flat buttons and simple icons. Focus 
          on content over chrome. Influenced by iOS 7 shift.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="card-title" style="color: var(--color-danger);">Twitter (2014 redesign)</h3>
        <p class="card-content">
          <strong>Platform:</strong> Web & Mobile<br>
          <strong>Year:</strong> 2014<br><br>
          Flattened interface with simple cards. Removed gradients and shadows. Clean, 
          content-focused design with colorful accents.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

